The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 August is 294,269 (33,916.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 August, there were 571 new confirmed cases (65.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 August, there were 711 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 20% (140 fewer cases).
